          <span class="cn-text">關於我們</span>
          <h1>About Quan Zhen<br>Cultural Society</h1>
          <p>Founded in Singapore in 2016, Quan Zhen Cultural Society is dedicated to the study, practice, and cultural preservation of the Quanzhen Longmen Taoist tradition — building a community of learners, practitioners, and custodians of heritage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Mission ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section section-paper">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="mission-grid">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:12px;">Our purpose</p>
            <h2 style="margin-bottom:16px;">Mission and Aims</h2>
            <p class="cn-text" style="font-size:13px; margin-bottom:24px;">宗旨與目標</p>
            <div class="gold-divider"></div>
            <p class="mission-intro">
              Quan Zhen Cultural Society exists to propagate, preserve, and transmit the Taoist Quanzhen Longmen tradition in Singapore. We serve as a living bridge between an ancient lineage and a modern society — nurturing the next generation of Taoist practitioners, leaders, and cultural custodians.
            </p>
            <p class="mission-intro" style="margin-top:16px;">
              We are open to all — whether you are a lifelong practitioner, a curious beginner, or simply someone who wishes to understand more about Taoism and its role in Chinese cultural heritage.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mission-aims">
            <div class="aim-item">
              <div class="aim-number">1</div>
              <p class="aim-text">Propagate Taoism through educational courses, public lectures, forums, and community events.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="aim-item">
              <div class="aim-number">2</div>
              <p class="aim-text">Serve as a platform for young Taoists — providing a space for learning, dialogue, and community connection.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="aim-item">
              <div class="aim-number">3</div>
              <p class="aim-text">Preserve the culture and practice of the Quanzhen Longmen Dragon Gate Sect's rites and rituals.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="aim-item">
              <div class="aim-number">4</div>
              <p class="aim-text">Instil leadership qualities among members and provide guidance and support to other Taoist organisations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="aim-item">
              <div class="aim-number">5</div>
              <p class="aim-text">Affiliate, liaise, and cooperate with similar bodies locally and overseas that share our objectives and aspirations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="aim-item">
              <div class="aim-number">6</div>
              <p class="aim-text">Train members in social service, offer Taoist teachings, and provide healthy and meaningful community activities.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Timeline ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section" style="background:#F0E6CF;">
      <div class="container">
        <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:64px; align-items:start;">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:12px;">Our story</p>
            <h2 style="margin-bottom:16px;">A Decade of Tradition</h2>
            <p class="cn-text" style="font-size:13px; margin-bottom:24px;">十年傳承</p>
            <div class="gold-divider"></div>
            <p style="color:#555; line-height:1.8; font-size:15px;">
              From a small circle of dedicated practitioners to a registered cultural society with a growing community, Quan Zhen Cultural Society has spent a decade building something that matters — a living tradition, practised with rigour and shared with openness.
            </p>
            <p style="color:#555; line-height:1.8; font-size:15px; margin-top:16px;">
              In 2026 we celebrated our 10th anniversary — a milestone that reflects not just the passage of time, but the depth of commitment from every member, teacher, and supporter who has been part of this journey.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">2016</div>
              <div class="timeline-title">Society established</div>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Quan Zhen Cultural Society was formally registered in Singapore, bringing together a community of Quanzhen Longmen practitioners committed to the study and preservation of the Taoist tradition.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">2016 – 2025</div>
              <div class="timeline-title">A decade of growth</div>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Nine years of rituals, scripture classes, public education, and community building — steadily growing our membership and deepening our practice across Singapore.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">2026</div>
              <div class="timeline-title">10th anniversary</div>
              <p class="timeline-desc">Quan Zhen Cultural Society celebrates a decade of service to the Taoist community in Singapore — marking ten years of heritage preserved, teachings shared, and a tradition kept alive.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

